%N A396861 The number of n-colorings of the faces of the truncated icosahedron up to rotation.
%C A396861 The truncated icosahedron is the classic soccer ball shape with 32 faces, of which 12 are pentagons and 20 are hexagons.
%C A396861 Colorings are counted up to the rotational icosahedral symmetry group of order 60.
%H A396861 Peter Kagey and William Keehn, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.26140">Escher's Cubes: Tiling the Faces of Polyhedra</a>, arXiv:2606.26140 [math.GM], 2026. See pp. 5, 42.
%H A396861 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Truncated_icosahedron">Truncated icosahedron</a>.
%F A396861 a(n) = (n^32 + 15*n^16 + 20*n^12 + 24*n^8)/60.
%t A396861 A396861[n_] := (n^32 + 15 n^16 + 20 n^12 + 24 n^8)/60
%Y A396861 Cf. A128766 (octahedron), A199406 (rhombic dodecahedron), A252704 (icosahedron), A252705 (dodecahedron), A274900 (rhombicuboctahedron), A337963 (rhombic triacontahedron), A378473 (tetrakis hexahedron), A378474 (disdyakis dodecahedron), A378475 (pentagonal icositetrahedron), A378476 (triakis icosahedron), A378477 (disdyakis triacontahedron), A378478 (pentagonal hexecontahedron), A396858 (pyritohedron).
